question:
District category contains Housing Estate, Shopping District, and Historic Downtown.
Supermarkets category contains Stop & Shop, Metro (Canada), and Fresh Thyme Market.
Product category contains Yogurt, Bread, and Cookies.
Ingredient category contains Food Coloring, Basil, and Paprika.
The number of each Housing Estate 's Fresh Thyme Market equals 0 times the difference of each Historic Downtown 's Stop & Shop and each Stop & Shop 's Bread.
The number of each Cookies 's Basil equals the difference of each Cookies 's Food Coloring and each Housing Estate 's Fresh Thyme Market.
The number of each Fresh Thyme Market 's Cookies equals each Metro (Canada) 's Yogurt.
The number of each Shopping District 's Stop & Shop equals each Shopping District 's Metro (Canada).
The number of each Metro (Canada) 's Yogurt equals 17 more than each Shopping District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Metro (Canada) 's Bread equals 7.
The number of each Shopping District 's Metro (Canada) equals 9.
The number of each Historic Downtown 's Stop & Shop equals 21 times each Stop & Shop 's Bread.
The number of each Bread 's Basil equals the sum of each Historic Downtown 's Stop & Shop and each Stop & Shop 's Bread.
The number of each Cookies 's Food Coloring equals the sum of each Bread 's Basil, each Historic Downtown 's Stop & Shop, and each Housing Estate 's Fresh Thyme Market.
The number of each Stop & Shop 's Bread equals 7.
The number of each Yogurt 's Food Coloring equals each Stop & Shop 's Bread.
How many Product does Fresh Thyme Market have?
solution:
Define each Shopping District 's Metro (Canada) as O; So O = 9.
Define each Shopping District 's Stop & Shop as L; So L = O = 9.
Define each Shopping District 's Supermarkets as z; So z = L + O = 9 + 9 = 18.
Define each Metro (Canada) 's Yogurt as C; So C = 17 + z = 17 + 18 = 12.
Define each Fresh Thyme Market 's Cookies as s; So s = C = 12.
Define each Fresh Thyme Market 's Product as F; So F = s = 12.
